verbose_text: Although the mechanisms associated with this phenomena are not clear, some families exhibit a high frequency of pituitary adenomas, and more recently, the presence of familial prolactinoma was associated with genes, such as the aryl hydrocarbon receptor interacting protein (AIP) gene,15 which in turn is related to inflammatory conditions.16 These data advocate for the key role of genetics in the development of pituitary adenomas, and the association between PRL and PolyA based on genetic background.
